    "technical_interpretation": "Given integers $a,b\\in\\mathbb{N}$, define the Cantor pairing function by \\[ \\langle a,b\\rangle = \\frac{(a+b)(a+b+1)}{2} + b. \\] Recursively pairing adjacent digits in a finite integer sequence yields a single natural number. Reducing the result modulo $153{,}600$ and adding one produces a DAANSphere address."
  },
